    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. What is Magic TV?</h2>
        <p>Magic TV is the home of interactive broadcasting formats powered by the Magic Code — an analog optical
            pattern that viewers scan with their mobile phone camera.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>No app required</li>
            <li>No installation</li>
            <li>Seamless integration into live content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>It transforms passive viewing into interactive participation with real-time engagement formats.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>A Magic Code appears during Stingray programming.</li>
            <li>Viewers scan the code using their phone's camera.</li>
            <li>They access interactive formats (e.g., quiz, vote, offer, loyalty).</li>
            <li>Stingray earns from user actions and paid interactions.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>No technical integration beyond displaying the code is required.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. Formats Tailored for Stingray</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Vote Your Vibe</strong> (Stingray Music): Viewers choose the next song or artist</li>
            <li><strong>Guess the Year</strong> (Stingray Retro): Quizzes about iconic hits</li>
            <li><strong>Magic Moment</strong> (Naturescape): Viewers collect favorite scenes</li>
            <li><strong>Pick Your Mood</strong> (Mood channels): Interactive mood selection with rewards</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each format drives engagement and unlocks monetization potential.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Why It’s Relevant to Stingray</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Adds new monetization to FAST & ambient content</li>
            <li>Enables mobile interaction with zero disruption</li>
            <li>Offers brand partners interactive ad campaigns</li>
            <li>Collects first-party data and engagement insights</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Magic TV brings interactivity to channels that traditionally had low user touchpoints.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
